      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the theory, but it seems hard to ignore that the \"original meaning\" often contradicts what people think is fair or just today. if the text is used to roll back rights that people rely on now, isn't it basically just a tool to keep the status quo rather than a real legal principle? it feels like it's more about ideology than actually following the law.",
